<1ST_LINE>r i PM-Spain-Bombs     05-02 0200</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Spain-Bombs,0205</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Two Bombs Explode In Barcelona; 16 Hurt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BARCELONA, Spain (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two bombs exploded early today in this
northeastern port city, injuring 16 people, two of them seriously.
A separatist group told a local newspaper it had planted the bombs.
   Police said one bomb placed near a window of a branch of the
Banco Central exploded at 2:05 a.m. (8:05 p.m. EDT Sunday) and
shattered the bank's windows.
   Soon after authorities arrived, a second bomb with more than
four pounds of shrapnel exploded in a nearby garbage container,
injuring 16 people.
   Two of them, a national policeman and a paramilitary civil
guard, were hospitalized with serious leg injuries. The other 14,
including four firemen and ten civilians, were treated for cuts at
a local hospital and released.
   The group Free Land, which supports independence for the
four-province region of Catalonia, of which Barcelona is the
capital, took responsibility for the two blasts in a telephone call
to the local Avui newspaper.
   The group has claimed responsibility for several attacks in
Barcelona, including a March 17 explosion at the British Consulate,
a bomb blast outside the U.S. Embassy last October and two attacks
on American businesses in 1987.
</TEXT>
