<HEAD>Marcos' Mother Hospitalized for Lung Infection</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MANILA, Philippines (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Deposed President Ferdinand Marcos'
95-year-old mother was admitted to a government hospital after she
refused to eat for three days, her doctor said today.
   Dona Josefa Edralin Marcos was dehydrated and had a slight lung
infection on Sunday when she was admitted to the Veterans Medical
Center in suburban Manila, according to Dr. Sergio Brillantes.
   He said Mrs. Marcos' condition ``could become serious'' because
of her age, as well as her diabetes and high blood sugar level.
   Mrs. Marcos stayed behind in February 1986 when a
military-civilian uprising drove her son to exile in Hawaii and
brought President Corazon Aquino to power. Mrs. Aquino has refused
to allow Marcos to come back, saying his return would not be good
for the country.
   Presidential spokesman Ralph Tagle would not comment when asked
if Mrs. Aquino would allow Marcos to return because of his mother's
failing health.
</TEXT>
