<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Jesse Jackson is the overwhelming favorite to
win Tuesday's District of Columbia primary and repeat one of his
two 1984 primary victories.
   Even front-runner Michael Dukakis' campaign concedes Jackson
will likely win most of the district's 16 delegates.
   ``There is no question that Jackson will take the majority,''
said Jim Nathanson, a city councilman who has been chief spokesman
