<2ND_LINE>AM-Spain-Bombs,0149</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Bomb Blasts Wound 16 In Barcelona</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BARCELONA, Spain (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two bomb explosions wounded 16 people in
Barcelona early Monday and a separatist group claimed
responsibility.
   The first bomb went off outside a branch of the Banco Central in
this northeastern port city, shattering the bank's windows, at 2:05
a.m. (8:05 p.m. EDT Sunday), police said.
   They said that soon after authorities arrived, a second bomb
containing more than four pounds of shrapnel exploded in a garbage
can, hurting 16 people.
   A national policeman and a paramilitary civil guard were
hospitalized with serious leg injuries. The other 14 injured _ four
firemen and 10 civilians _ were treated for cuts.
   The organization Free Land, which wants independence for the
four-province region of Catalonia, of which Barcelona is the
capital, claimed responsibility for the explosions in a telephone
call to the local Avui newspaper.
</TEXT>
