<HEAD>Condition of Aged Marcos Mother Deteriorating</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MANILA, Philippines (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The 95-year-old mother of deposed
President Ferdinand Marcos is suffering from pneumonia and diabetes
and her condition is deteriorating, her doctor said Tuesday.
   Josefa Edralin-Marcos was admitted on Sunday to the Veterans
Medical Center in suburban Quezon City after she refused to eat for
three days.
   ``She is not responding to medication ... probably due to her
weakened resistance,'' Dr. Sergio Brillantes, director of the
government-run hospital, said in a radio interview.
   Brillantes said a son, Pacifico Marcos, and daughter, Mrs.
Fortuna Barba, were at their mother's bedside.
   Mrs. Marcos stayed behind in February 1986 when a
military-civilian uprising ousted her son Ferdinand, who went into
him into exile in Hawaii.
   The uprising brought President Corazon Aquino to power. She has
refused to allow Marcos to come back.
   In Honolulu, Marcos spokesman Gemmo Trinidad said the former
president was aware of his mother's condition.
