<1ST_LINE>r i AM-AircraftDoor     05-02 0152</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Aircraft Door,0154</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Door Falls From Boeing 727, Lands In Yard</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A door fell Monday from a Boeing 727, landed in
the back yard of a suburban home and demolished a fence, officials
said. No injuries were reported.
   Authorities were investigating the incident, which occurred when
the Icelandair jet approached a runway at Heathrow Airport. The
Boeing was carying 76 passengers and six crew members from
Reykjavik to London.
   The 66-pound metal door, measuring about 6 square feet, had
covered the wheel wells, said Oliver Smith, Icelandair's station
manager at Heathrow. It fell from the starboard wing of the jet and
landed behind a house in Pinner, 12 miles northwest of central
London.
   The aircraft landed without problem. Smith said the door would
be examined.
   ``Some of the fittings that hold it on appear to have sheared
off but we have no idea how it happened,'' he said.
</TEXT>
