<HEAD>31 Killed in Bus Accident</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: CORRECTS province name in lead graf to Shanxi, not Chanxi. No
pickup</NOTE>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A bus carrying high school students and teachers
on a sightseeing trip in central Shanxi province overturned on a
winding mountain road and 31 people were killed, the Xinhua news
agency reported Monday.
   The official agency said 50 people were injured in the accident
Saturday in Jiaocheng county.
   Xinhua said the driver did not have a license to operate the
vehicle and the bus was packed with 89 people although it was
designed to carry only 47. It did not say what happened to the
driver.
</TEXT>
